---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
import { Navbar } from "@/components/Navbar"
import { Footer } from "@/components/Footer"
import { absoluteUrl, breadcrumbJsonLd, organizationJsonLd } from "@/lib/seo"
---

<Layout
  seo={{
    title: "Privacy Policy - LobbyStack",
    description:
      "Privacy Policy for LobbyStack, including call, SMS, consent, appointment, account, billing, analytics, and support data.",
    canonicalPath: "/privacy/",
    noindex: true,
    jsonLd: [
      organizationJsonLd(),
      breadcrumbJsonLd([
        { name: "Home", path: "/" },
        { name: "Privacy Policy", path: "/privacy/" },
      ]),
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "@id": absoluteUrl("/privacy/#webpage"),
        name: "Privacy Policy - LobbyStack",
        url: absoluteUrl("/privacy/"),
        description:
          "Privacy Policy for LobbyStack, including call, SMS, consent, appointment, account, billing, analytics, and support data.",
      },
    ],
  }}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <section class="border-b border-border/60">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 md:py-20">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">
          Last updated: May 11, 2026
        </p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p
          class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground md:text-lg"
        >
          This Privacy Policy explains how Lobbystack Inc. ("Lobbystack,"
          "LobbyStack," "we," "our," or "us") collects, uses, discloses, and
          protects personal information when you visit our website, use
          LobbyStack Cloud, communicate through LobbyStack-powered calls or SMS,
          contact support, or interact with our services.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-6 text-muted-foreground">
          This Policy is intended to support transparency for business
          customers, callers, message recipients, website visitors, and
          open-source/self-hosted users. If your business uses LobbyStack to
          communicate with its customers, you are responsible for providing any
          additional notices required for your own use of the service.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-10 px-6 py-12 md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] md:py-16"
    >
      <aside class="hidden md:block">
        <nav class="sticky top-8 space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#scope">Scope</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#collect">Information</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#sms">SMS consent</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#use">Use</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#share">Sharing</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#retention">Retention</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#rights">Rights</a>
          <a class="block hover:text-foreground" href="#contact">Contact</a>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <article class="legal-copy max-w-none">
        <section id="scope">
          <h2>1. Scope and our role</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack provides a business AI receptionist platform for calls,
            SMS, appointment booking, routing, summaries, customer intake,
            knowledge-based answers, and related workflows. We may process
            personal information as a business/controller for our own website,
            accounts, billing, security, support, and marketing operations. We
            may also process personal information on behalf of business
            customers that use LobbyStack to communicate with their callers,
            customers, leads, patients, clients, or other end users.
          </p>
          <p>
            When a business uses LobbyStack to communicate with you, that
            business is responsible for deciding how and why your information is
            used. Please contact that business directly for questions about its
            own privacy practices.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="collect">
          <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
          <h3>Account and business information</h3>
          <p>
            We collect information such as names, email addresses, phone
            numbers, business names, business addresses, roles, login details,
            account settings, authorized users, support preferences, compliance
            information, and billing contacts.
          </p>
          <h3>Call, SMS, and contact information</h3>
          <p>
            LobbyStack may process phone numbers, caller IDs, call metadata,
            call recordings, transcripts, summaries, voicemails, SMS message
            content, message metadata, opt-in and opt-out status, consent
            records, contact profiles, notes, conversation history, appointment
            details, requested services, routing decisions, escalation outcomes,
            and related operational records.
          </p>
          <h3>Business content and knowledge data</h3>
          <p>
            Customers may upload or connect business information, FAQs, service
            descriptions, prices, hours, locations, policies, calendars,
            documents, website content, scripts, rules, and other materials used
            to configure the AI receptionist.
          </p>
          <h3>Billing, payment, and tax information</h3>
          <p>
            We and our payment processor, currently Polar, may collect billing
            details, payment method information, transaction history, plan
            details, metered usage, invoices, tax information, and payment
            status. We do not store full payment card numbers unless a payment
            processor provides that service on our behalf.
          </p>
          <h3>Website, device, analytics, and support information</h3>
          <p>
            We may collect IP addresses, device and browser information, pages
            viewed, referring pages, interactions, approximate location, cookies
            or similar identifiers, product telemetry, logs, diagnostic
            information, crash reports, support tickets, emails, and other
            communications with us.
          </p>
          <h3>Referral and affiliate information</h3>
          <p>
            If you arrive through an affiliate or referral link, we may process
            referral codes, click timestamps, referring pages, local storage or
            similar identifiers, signup attribution, commission records, and
            payout contact details to operate the affiliate program, prevent
            abuse, calculate commissions, and maintain payout records.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="sms">
          <h2>3. SMS consent and messaging privacy</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack supports non-marketing operational and conversational SMS
            messages, such as customer inquiry replies, appointment
            confirmations, missed-call follow-up, service updates, support
            messages, reminders, routing, intake, and related business
            workflows. Message frequency varies. Message and data rates may
            apply. Message recipients can reply <strong>STOP</strong> to opt out and
            <strong>HELP</strong> for help where supported, or contact
            <a href="mailto:support@lobbystack.com">support@lobbystack.com</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            We may process SMS consent records, opt-in sources, opt-out status,
            message content, timestamps, phone numbers, carrier metadata, and
            delivery information to provide and operate messaging features,
            comply with carrier and A2P/10DLC requirements, prevent abuse, and
            honor opt-out requests.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>
              We do not sell, rent, or share SMS opt-in data or consent
              information with third parties or affiliates for their marketing
              or promotional purposes.
            </strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="use">
          <h2>4. How we use information</h2>
          <p>We use personal information to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide, operate, secure, maintain, and improve LobbyStack.</li>
            <li>
              Answer calls, process SMS, generate summaries, route requests, and
              support appointment workflows.
            </li>
            <li>
              Configure AI responses using customer-provided business
              information and instructions.
            </li>
            <li>
              Manage accounts, authentication, billing, taxes, plans, usage, and
              support.
            </li>
            <li>
              Process opt-ins, opt-outs, consent records, and telecommunications
              compliance requirements.
            </li>
            <li>
              Detect, prevent, and investigate spam, abuse, fraud, security
              incidents, and misuse.
            </li>
            <li>
              Communicate about service updates, security, billing, support, and
              administrative matters.
            </li>
            <li>
              Analyze service performance, reliability, errors, and feature
              usage.
            </li>
            <li>
              Comply with legal, regulatory, contractual, provider, carrier, and
              accounting obligations.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We may use de-identified, aggregated, or statistical information to
            analyze and improve the service where it does not identify a person,
            business customer, or end user.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="ai-processing">
          <h2>5. AI and automated processing</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack may send prompts, business context, call audio,
            transcripts, SMS content, customer instructions, and related
            workflow data to AI model providers or AI infrastructure providers
            to generate responses, summaries, classifications, routing
            decisions, or other automated outputs. AI outputs can be inaccurate
            or incomplete, and business customers are responsible for
            configuring appropriate human review and fallback procedures.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="google-oauth-calendar">
          <h2>5.1 Google OAuth and Google Calendar integration</h2>
          <p>
            When you connect your Google account in LobbyStack (for example via
            Settings → Integrations), we use Google OAuth to access your Google
            account and to manage scheduling on the specific Google Calendar
            you select.
          </p>

          <p>
            We request Google permissions that allow us to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Read calendar availability by accessing events on your selected
              calendar (scope: <strong>calendar.readonly</strong> /
              <strong> calendar.events</strong>).
            </li>
            <li>
              Create, update, and delete appointment events on your selected
              calendar (scope: <strong>calendar.events</strong>) when
              appointments are booked, rescheduled, or cancelled.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            <strong>Google user data we access.</strong> We access data related
            to your connected Google account (such as your account identifier
            and email, when available) and calendar event data needed to
            calculate busy time and to synchronize appointment bookings.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>How we use it.</strong> We use this data to list calendars
            during setup (so you can choose which calendar should receive
            bookings), keep availability up to date, and ensure our booking
            records stay consistent with your selected calendar.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Storage and protection.</strong> To perform sync and booking
            actions over time, we store the OAuth tokens required for the
            integration in our backend. Tokens are encrypted at rest. If you
            disconnect Google Calendar in LobbyStack, we delete the stored
            calendar connection and remove the appointment events we created
            as part of disconnect processing.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Disclosure / sharing.</strong> We disclose the minimum
            necessary information to the Google Calendar API to complete the
            requested integration features. We also share data with our hosting,
            database, and security providers as needed to operate the service,
            as described elsewhere in this Privacy Policy.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Data restrictions.</strong> We use Google user data only to
            provide and improve the Google Calendar integration features. We do
            not sell Google user data or use it for targeted advertising or
            advertising personalization.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="share">
          <h2>6. How we disclose information</h2>
          <p>
            We disclose information only as needed for the purposes described in
            this Policy, including to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Telephony, SMS, carrier, and number providers.</li>
            <li>AI model and speech processing providers.</li>
            <li>
              Hosting, database, storage, infrastructure, monitoring, and
              security providers.
            </li>
            <li>
              Polar or other payment processors, billing systems, tax tools, and
              accounting providers.
            </li>
            <li>
              Email, support, customer communication, and notification
              providers.
            </li>
            <li>Analytics and product telemetry providers.</li>
            <li>
              Calendar, document, website import, and other integration
              providers you connect.
            </li>
            <li>
              Professional advisers, auditors, insurers, and legal or regulatory
              authorities where required.
            </li>
            <li>
              Successors or participants in a merger, financing, acquisition,
              reorganization, or sale of assets.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not sell personal information in the ordinary sense of that
            word. We do not share SMS opt-in data or consent information with
            third parties or affiliates for their marketing or promotional
            purposes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="cookies">
          <h2>7. Cookies and analytics</h2>
          <p>
            We may use cookies, local storage, pixels, analytics tools, and
            similar technologies to operate the website and app, remember
            preferences, understand product usage, improve performance, detect
            abuse, and measure marketing effectiveness. You can control some
            cookies through your browser settings, but disabling cookies may
            affect service functionality. See our
            <a href="/cookie-policy/">Cookie Policy</a> for more detail about
            the cookies and similar technologies we use.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="retention">
          <h2>8. Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain personal information for as long as needed to provide the
            service, maintain accounts, support billing and tax records, comply
            with legal and provider obligations, resolve disputes, enforce
            agreements, prevent abuse, and maintain security. Retention periods
            may vary based on the type of data, account settings, customer
            configuration, backup cycles, legal obligations, and operational
            needs.
          </p>
          <p>
            Business customers may be able to delete or export certain account
            data from the service. Some records may remain in backups, logs,
            compliance records, invoices, or audit trails for a limited period
            or where retention is legally required.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="security">
          <h2>9. Security</h2>
          <p>
            We use administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards
            designed to protect personal information. No method of transmission
            or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute
            security. You are responsible for protecting your credentials,
            managing authorized users, configuring access controls, and using
            the service appropriately.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="transfers">
          <h2>10. Cross-border processing</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack is operated from Canada, and personal information may be
            processed in Canada, the United States, and other jurisdictions
            where we or our service providers operate. Those jurisdictions may
            have privacy laws different from the laws where you live. Where
            required, we use contractual, technical, and organizational measures
            intended to protect personal information transferred across borders.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="rights">
          <h2>11. Privacy rights and requests</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on where you live and your relationship with LobbyStack,
            you may have rights to access, correct, delete, export, restrict, or
            object to certain processing of your personal information. You may
            also have rights to withdraw consent where processing is based on
            consent, subject to legal or contractual limits.
          </p>
          <p>
            To make a privacy request, contact
            <a href="mailto:support@lobbystack.com">support@lobbystack.com</a>.
            We may need to verify your identity and, if your information is
            controlled by a business customer, refer your request to that
            customer or process it according to that customer's instructions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="children">
          <h2>12. Children</h2>
          <p>
            LobbyStack is a business service and is not directed to children. We
            do not knowingly collect personal information from children through
            our own website or hosted account signup. If you believe a child has
            provided personal information to us, contact us so we can review the
            request.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="changes">
          <h2>13. Changes to this Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If changes are
            material, we will provide reasonable notice, such as by posting an
            updated Policy, updating the date above, emailing account contacts,
            or notifying users in the service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="terms">
          <h2>14. Terms of Service</h2>
          <p>
            Your use of LobbyStack is also governed by our
            <a href="/terms/">Terms of Service</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="contact">
          <h2>15. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions or requests about this Privacy Policy can be sent to
            Lobbystack Inc. at
            <a href="mailto:support@lobbystack.com">support@lobbystack.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
